task.summary:
Changed version to 1.5.0. Added documentation. Cleaned up tiles.html.
Fixed doc generator to not put empty parentheses on predicates.

Extended data_predicates.pl with undo. Updated version to 1.5.2.
Changed console.pl to use new data_predicates/4. data_predicates.pl: changed to data_predicates/4 from /3 to add 'option' (undoable, ephemeral) argument; added use of undo module; added cuts for performance optimization; added 'action' predicate generation for get, set, update, and clear. Extended object.pl with >>$/2 - this is >>/2 with a trailing cut; added cuts for performance optimization. Added undo.pl to support undoing assertions (primarily of data_predicates data). bootstrap_js.pl: added cuts to partition/4 and key_partition/4 to prevent sort/2 from creating needless choicepoints. Fixed proscript_interpreter_terminal.js to use $.terminal.escape_formatting on strings to be output in the terminal (fixes a bug with strings containing '[[' due to nested lists). Updated JQuery terminal to 2.9.0.

Added WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope interface and random builtins.
Optimized sort/2 to check if the 'input' list is already in sorted order. Added random/1 and random_between/3.

Fixed compare_terms to deref args and handle lists correctly.
Extended keysort/2 with presorted check. Added term compare tests.
Fixed sort check to remove duplicates.

Added some builtin doc. Fixed writeq escape of \.
Added doc for arithmetic comparisons and 'is'/2, term comparisons, atom chars/codes, number codes, char conversion. Fixed quote_atom function in read.js to escape \. Fixed generate_predicate_doc.pl generate_pred_sidenav_entry/2 and generate_pred_cat_sidenav_entry/3 to use writeq for Label and Pred.

Added doc for many predicates. Fixed gensym to increment counter.
Extended generate_pred_cat_sidenav_entry/3 to convert category terms to display strings with '-' replaced by space (' ').
Converted memory refs in foreign.js to always deref, using get_arg.
Converted more memory[VAL(...)...] refs to always deref, using get_arg.

Version 1.5.4. Fixed cut and neck_cut to set HB. Fixed a module bug in data_predicates.
Fixed yield/0 to handle concurrent invocation of proscriptls function - added wamYielded to WAM state.

Fixed handling of negative integers.
Fixed several bugs in handling of negative integers. This included '-1 @> 1' being true. Generally replaced VAL(x) with PL_get_integer(x), where PL_get_integer(x) uses 'VAL(x) - (1 << WORD_BITS)' to get value of 'x' as a negative integer and just 'VAL(x)' when value of 'x' is a positive integer. 'x' represents a negative integer if and only if '(VAL(x) & (1 << (WORD_BITS-1))) === (1 << (WORD_BITS-1))'. Also replaced code to create integer term from integer 'x' with 'PL_put_integer(x)' => '(x & ((1 << WORD_BITS)-1)) ^ (TAG_INT << WORD_BITS)'. foreign.js: Fixed evaluate_expression, integer_list_to_term_array, and compare_terms to use PL_get_integer. object_property.js: Fixed getIntegerPropertyValue to use PL_get_integer. read.js: Fixed format_term and expression_to_term to use PL_get_integer. record.js: Fixed record_term to use PL_put_integer. stream.js: Fixed predicate_get_code, predicate_get_byte, predicate_peek_code, and predicate_peek_byte to use PL_put_integer. tests.pl: Added sort(4) test to check sorting of negative integers.

Object method spec fixes. Extended MouseEvent API. Added max_depth option to write_term; used it in debugger and repl. Optimized sort/2 and keysort/2.
Added 'string' as a result type in object method. read.js: Added max_depth to parse_term_options function, added depth arg and max_depth checking to format_term function, added atom(X) as pseudo-stream to predicate_write_term function. web_interfaces.js: Fixed getPropertyPriority, getPropertyValue, removeProperty, and setProperty arg types from 'atom' to 'string', completed mouseEvent properties (e.g. altKey, button, screenX), added getModifierState method to mouseevent. Changed sort/2 and keysort/2 in bootstrap_js.pl to use difference list instead of append/3. Changed debugger to use write_term/3 with max_depth(5). Changed print_bindings_1/1 (used by top level repl/1) to use write_term/2 with max_depth(5) and quoted(true) for the Value of the binding. Added write_term test to tests.pl.
